your AdAttributionKit implementation. To get the most out of this session, we recommend first watching “Meet AdAttributionKit.”","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"references":{"WWDC25-Icon.png":{"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-Icon.png"}]},"WWDCNotes.png":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"WWDC25.jpg":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25.jpg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDC25.jpg","type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC24-10060-Meet-AdAttributionKit":{"type":"topic","title":"Meet AdAttributionKit","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Introducing AdAttributionKit, a new iOS framework for privacy-preserving ad attribution. Learn how AdAttributionKit supports re-engagement, click-through attribution (including support for custom creative), JWS formatted impressions and postbacks, and more. We’ll provide insight into testing your AdAttributionKit implementation and deep-dive into code snippets and best practices for adopting AdAttributionKit."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC24-10060-Meet-AdAttributionKit","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc24-10060-meet-adattributionkit","kind":"article","role":"sampleCode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-246-Integrate-privacy-into-your-development-process":{"role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-246-Integrate-privacy-into-your-development-process","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to build privacy into your apps from the planning stages through deployment. We’ll cover practical ways to integrate privacy at each step of the development lifecycle, focusing on data minimization, on-device processing, and transparency and control. You’ll discover how to use Apple’s tools and frameworks to protect user data and create a privacy-respecting app experience."}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-246-integrate-privacy-into-your-development-process","kind":"article","type":"topic","title":"Integrate privacy into your development process"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"title":"Learn More…","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"type":"link","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","abstract":[{"text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/221":{"type":"download","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/221","checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/221"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25":{"title":"WWDC25","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 26, Swift 6.2, iOS\/macOS\/tvOS\/visionOS 26."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"code":"Foundation Models","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"AlarmKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"PermissionKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and more."}],"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC25.jpg"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25","role":"collectionGroup"}}}